<subSubSection id="219ECF9FB5E0A884F7B08599B988DC3E" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="F833340A02E7D9E8318E9223C2BF9B16" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="437F1E25421E8D384E4C7612CD36C9EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
The specific epithet 
<emphasis id="F8D7844528C81DB66885179ACD2A4CD9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">magnifica</emphasis>
is derived from the Latin adjective 
<emphasis id="4768D0FAC5F746A6271B6BA45311FB58" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">magnicus</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="2CABB28CB5192812FC888DDC8756D5AF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">a</emphasis>
- 
<emphasis id="18C0881CA8D23AA2182EBD9BA162C370" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">um</emphasis>
(a. splendid, magnificent) and is named for the magnificent, showy, vivid fuchsia-pink flowers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="56D811AD2ABEE1EC8EDCAF96BC99E611" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" type="distribution and ecology">
<paragraph id="8229A7A7BAC51DBFD838F77DE02C2FD3" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Distribution and ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C1785934F1394601ECAC7FE08E6FC6D" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="019C2DC930FF18EB8FD79D6E06D4AFF9" authorityName="Schrire &amp; V. R. Clark" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera magnifica" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis id="FC89A32293F2D0BA08C4EAC50652DE3E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Indigofera magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confined to the summit plateau of the Toorberg-Koudeveld-Meelberg in the western Sneeuberg, between 1700-2150 m. The species is occasional to abundant, found exclusively on the dolerite-derived loamy-clays and black turf soils typical of this plateau. The vegetation type is Karoo Escarpment Grassland (Gh1, 
<bibRefCitation id="888A13BE1B7D457329CF15758413F8BB" author="Mucina, L" journalOrPublisher="Strelitzia" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 807" refId="B10" refString="Mucina, L, Rutherford, MC, 2006. The Vegetation of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Strelitzia Vol. 19: 1 - 807" title="The Vegetation of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland." volume="Vol. 19" year="2006">Mucina and Rutherford 2006</bibRefCitation>
), typical of high altitudes in the Sneeuberg mountain complex, with the dominant grass species being 
<taxonomicName id="1CF2048435AA3FF0DD27D4CA4B0F44AD" authorityName="N.P.Barker &amp; H.P.Linder" authorityYear="2010" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Tenaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tenaxia" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4EE3B2151428DAF1226934840D51D7B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Tenaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="9EF3A2A163BEF28001D99A448FACA8FA" authorityName="H.J.Conert" authorityYear="1970" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merxmuellera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Merxmuellera" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2D184E026FEA6D6EB7F4F28DC0C094C3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Merxmuellera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="14643DCCFDAAE652C70876CF1A1DCD9A" authorityName="Conert" authorityYear="1970" baseAuthorityName="Nees" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Merxmuellera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="disticha" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="disticha">
<emphasis id="42F2935E33127360B4AADF6EFA207924" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">disticha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nees) N.P. Barker &amp; H.P. Linder. 
<taxonomicName id="08E900A5DA8F1DBC900323537E7DE6AD" authorityName="Schrire &amp; V. R. Clark" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Leguminosae" genus="Indigofera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Indigofera magnifica" order="Fabales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis id="F645778EACD02B2A308A25410FDF4386" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Indigofera magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is particularly abundant on the highest parts of the plateau near the eastern and southern scarps, where it forms large colonies. It compliments a suite of several local endemics only found in the western Sneeuberg, including 
<taxonomicName id="FED9BE3E5DEF66970AEA038EE4D4FA1A" authorityName="Bartling &amp; H.L.Wendland" authorityYear="1824" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Acmadenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Acmadenia" order="Sapindales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A2876315DB10105DBDB61AE3DB5F2315" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Acmadenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., 
<taxonomicName id="5797C777C01C44CC001EDC2CAA1661B7" authorityName="E. G. H. Oliver" authorityYear="1994" baseAuthorityName="Bolus" class="Eudicots" family="Ericaceae" genus="Erica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Erica passerinoides" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="passerinoides">
<emphasis id="A97C88369420DC2F5931A68E66105624" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Erica passerinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bolus) E.G.H. Oliv., 
<taxonomicName id="98BACDE458DBEF6F433E081F5C6FABF0" authorityName="B. Nordenst" authorityYear="1961" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Euryops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Euryops dentatus" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="649BE9EE7E30C9088F2801D389F398E1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Euryops dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
B. Nord. and 
<taxonomicName id="75CD3989D95BC6BB479075A26F38E075" authorityName="Rourke &amp; V. R. Clark" authorityYear="2013" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Proteaceae" genus="Faurea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Faurea recondita" order="Proteales" pageId="0" pageNumber="29" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="recondita">
<emphasis id="982CC0F0E19413DB7A27B367187AB596" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="29">Faurea recondita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Rourke &amp; V.R. Clark (
<bibRefCitation id="1FD921BD956CBD5BB16316C4DBDF7E3F" author="Clark, VR" journalOrPublisher="South African Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" pagination="196 - 238" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.sajb.2008.10.010" refId="B4" refString="Clark, VR, Barker, NP, Mucina, L, 2009. The Sneeuberg: A new centre of endemism on the Great Escarpment, South Africa. South African Journal of Botany 75: 196 - 238, DOI: 10.1016/j.sajb.2008.10.010" title="The Sneeuberg: A new centre of endemism on the Great Escarpment, South Africa." url="10.1016/j.sajb.2008.10.010" volume="75" year="2009">Clark et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63FE975B81CB8E7BB46855E3DEC351A8" author="Clark, VR" journalOrPublisher="SpringerPlus" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" pagination="56 - 66" publicationUrl="10.1186/2193-1801-1-56" refId="B6" refString="Clark, VR, Perera, SJ, Stiller, M, Stirton, CH, Weston, PH, Stoev, P, Coombs, G, Morris, DB, Ratnayake-Perera, D, Barker, NP, McGregor, GK, 2012. A rapid multi-disciplinary biodiversity assessment of the Kamdebooberge (Sneeuberg, Eastern Cape, South Africa): implications for conservation. SpringerPlus 1: 56 - 66, DOI: 10.1186/2193-1801-1-56" title="A rapid multi-disciplinary biodiversity assessment of the Kamdebooberge (Sneeuberg, Eastern Cape, South Africa): implications for conservation." url="10.1186/2193-1801-1-56" volume="1" year="2012">2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="3737DFC03582A9BB6DF83FFC4369B9EA" author="Rourke, JP" journalOrPublisher="South African Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="34" pagination="34 - 38" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.sajb.2013.03.009" refId="B14" refString="Rourke, JP, Clark, VR, Barker, NP, 2013. Faurea recondita (Proteaceae): A new species from the Sneeuberg Centre of Endemism, South Africa. South African Journal of Botany 87: 34 - 38, DOI: 10.1016/j.sajb.2013.03.009" title="Faurea recondita (Proteaceae): A new species from the Sneeuberg Centre of Endemism, South Africa." url="10.1016/j.sajb.2013.03.009" volume="87" year="2013">Rourke et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
